# probability_edit_smoke.numos — Phase 6D: edit a ProbabilityApp parameter numerically.
#
# Unlike probability_smoke.numos (which only opens the app at its default normal
# parameters mu=0, sigma=1, x=0), this script proves ProbabilityApp is INTERACTABLE
# *through the numeric editor*: it opens the focused mu field, types a real value 2.5,
# commits it, and lets the app recompute the normal PDF/CDF and redraw the bell curve,
# so the rendered frame visibly differs from default (the curve centers at 2.5).
#
# Phase 6D fixed the digit-entry bug. Previously the numeric edit-buffer path did NOT
# work because digit detection used the range test `code >= NUM_0 && code <= NUM_9`
# (ProbabilityApp.cpp). The KeyCode enum declares the digits NON-contiguously and out of
# order — NUM_7..NUM_9 (row 3), NUM_4..NUM_6 (row 4), NUM_1..NUM_3 then NUM_0 last near
# ENTER (row 5) — so NUM_0 > NUM_9 and that range was always empty (KeyCodes.h:68-77);
# digit keys were silently ignored. The fix replaces the range test (and the
# ordering-dependent `code - NUM_0` arithmetic) with the explicit, order-independent
# helper keyCodeDigitValue(KeyCode) (KeyCodes.h), so digits register in the editor.
#
# Edit flow (focus starts on mu, mu=0, ProbabilityApp.cpp constructor):
#   * ENTER (nav mode) opens the editor; startEdit() pre-fills the buffer with the
#     current value formatted "%.4g" — i.e. "0" for mu=0 (ProbabilityApp.cpp:350-363).
#   * DEL clears that pre-filled "0" so the typed value starts clean.
#   * Digits and DOT append to the buffer ("2", "2.", "2.5"); this exercises real
#     numeric + decimal entry, the path that was previously dead.
#   * ENTER commits via finishEdit(): atof("2.5") -> _mu=2.5, then recompute() redraws
#     the PDF/CDF labels and the bell curve (ProbabilityApp.cpp:375-388). Pure <cmath>
#     ProbEngine: no Giac/CAS, no PSRAM, no LittleFS. Fully deterministic.
#
# As with every emulator screen the only volatile region is the StatusBar clock
# (HH:MM). This phase makes NO golden claim; the screenshot is a CANDIDATE for human
# review only (a clock mask is added by the human at promotion time, rect 4,6,37,13).
#
# Timing notes (deterministic, step-ms 16):
#   * 200 frames -> splash done, in launcher.
#   * 60 frames  -> Probability screen load + fade settles after open_app.
#   * one frame per key command (1 command/frame).
#   * 120 frames -> recompute + bell-curve redraw settles.
#
# Run:
#   program --headless --deterministic --script tests/emulator/scripts/probability_edit_smoke.numos \
#           --frames 800 --screenshot out/probability_edit_smoke.ppm --quiet
# Exit codes: 0 ok · 2 script/parse error · 3 screenshot write error · 4 assertion failure.

log "probability_edit_smoke: waiting for launcher"
wait 200

# Open Probability (emulator launchApp id 5 — same id as the launcher's Probability card).
open_app Probability
wait 60
assert_app Probability

# Edit the focused mu field numerically: open the editor, clear the pre-filled "0",
# type 2.5, and commit. finishEdit() sets mu=2.5 and recompute()s the PDF/CDF + curve.
key enter
key del
key 2
key dot
key 5
key enter
wait 120

# Screenshot FIRST so the artifact exists even if a later assertion fails.
screenshot out/probability_edit_smoke.ppm
log "probability_edit_smoke: screenshot captured (mu typed to 2.5, PDF/CDF recomputed)"

assert_app Probability
log "probability_edit_smoke: assertion passed (Probability active)"
